[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = SyntheticLikelihood2","category":"page"},{"location":"#SyntheticLikelihood2","page":"Home","title":"SyntheticLikelihood2","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for SyntheticLikelihood2.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [SyntheticLikelihood2]","category":"page"},{"location":"#SyntheticLikelihood2.DoubleKernel","page":"Home","title":"SyntheticLikelihood2.DoubleKernel","text":"Naive conditional kernel density estimator. Uses kernel density estimates for p(x, θ) and p(θ), and estimates the likelihood with p(x, θ)/p(θ).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#SyntheticLikelihood2.Prior","page":"Home","title":"SyntheticLikelihood2.Prior","text":"Struct to hold prior distributions. v is a vector of distributions from Distributions.jl. Univariate and/or multivariate distributions can be used. Each element in the vector is assumed to be independent.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#SyntheticLikelihood2.cut_at-Tuple{AbstractVector{T} where T, Vector{Int64}}","page":"Home","title":"SyntheticLikelihood2.cut_at","text":"'Cut' vector at specified indexes, to form a vector of vectors. Note the cut occurs after the index, so [1] would cut between index 1 and 2 in the vector.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyntheticLikelihood2.gaussian_simulator-Tuple{Random.AbstractRNG, Vector{Float64}}","page":"Home","title":"SyntheticLikelihood2.gaussian_simulator","text":"Simulate a three dimensional Gaussian mean vector θ. The covariance is diagonal, and fixed to σ=0.1. Parameter vector θ is the mean vector of the Gaussian\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyntheticLikelihood2.in_prior_support-Tuple{Prior, AbstractVector{Float64}}","page":"Home","title":"SyntheticLikelihood2.in_prior_support","text":"Check if a parameter vector falls within the prior support.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyntheticLikelihood2.log_prior_gradient-Tuple{Prior, Vector{Float64}}","page":"Home","title":"SyntheticLikelihood2.log_prior_gradient","text":"Automatic differentiation to get prior gradient.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyntheticLikelihood2.log_prior_hessian-Tuple{Prior, Vector{Float64}}","page":"Home","title":"SyntheticLikelihood2.log_prior_hessian","text":"Automatic differentiation to get prior Hessian.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyntheticLikelihood2.prior_cov-Tuple{Prior}","page":"Home","title":"SyntheticLikelihood2.prior_cov","text":"Covariance matrix of the prior.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyntheticLikelihood2.prior_logpdf-Tuple{Prior, Vector{Float64}}","page":"Home","title":"SyntheticLikelihood2.prior_logpdf","text":"Evaluate the density of the prior at θ.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyntheticLikelihood2.propose-Tuple{Random.AbstractRNG, Prior}","page":"Home","title":"SyntheticLikelihood2.propose","text":"Sample parameters from the prior. Note that if n is provided, a matrix is returned with n columns.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SyntheticLikelihood2.@loopify-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SyntheticLikelihood2.@loopify","text":"Convenience macro to define a method for a simulator that allows simulating in     batches. i.e. it takes simulator(rng::AbstractRNG, θ::Vector{Float64}) and     wraps it in a for loop to get simulator(rng::AbstractRNG,     θ::Matrix{Float64}).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"macro"}]
